# Git — default commit and push

When implementation work is complete and the user has not said "do not push":

1. **Do not ask** whether to commit or push — do both by default.
2. Stage relevant changes, write a concise commit message (why, not just what), commit, then `git push origin` (current branch).
3. Only skip commit/push when the user explicitly says not to, or when there are no changes.
4. Never force-push to main/master unless explicitly requested.
